1. IN Jira 'Settings' > 'Products' > 'Application links' prompt,
  ENTER second Jira instance address & SELECT 'Create New link' (EXAMPLE: 'https://targetinstance.atlassian.net')
  
2. IN remote Jira application 'Connections' prompt,
  SELECT 'OAuth' for both 'Outgoing' and 'Incoming' (NOTE: You don't need to create OAuth token, Jira gives you a default one)
  
3. IN targeted Jira instance, EXECUTE 1 & 2 for the initial instance

(NOTE: A person doing that should have admin rights in the targeted instance. A successful link will be marked with 'Connected' status)
